p: \rAll right, Taen, your commission is done.
\rI'm wiping my hands of it.\nI don't want to be involved with this creepy cult stuff anymore.
\bI've wired $1,000,000 to your PokeBank account, as agreed.
\bNow show me the suit I paid for.
\rThe armor has been made to your exact specifications.
\rTheoretically, it should increase the defensive stats of a Pokemon that wears it.
\rI did a bit of research. The only Pokemon that fits your measurements is... well, Zekrom.
\rHarmony told me that you had Kyurem back in the Suntouched City Gym.
\rDo you honestly expect me to believe you have Zekrom too?
\bI really don't care if you believe it. The truth is the truth.
\bGreat work. The armor looks sturdy and functional.
\rI've heard stories about Zekrom, but I never thought I'd see it myself.
\rHow is it that you've caught two legendary Pokemon?\nMost people never even see one in their lifetimes!
\bMaster Balls. Lots and lots of Master Balls.
\bI don't try to coax or convince them to join us.\nHave you seen how other groups operate?
\bThey just ask them to join. It's no wonder they never succeed.
\bCommon sense, come on. A strong Pokeball is so much more effective than messing around.
\bAnyways, it seems to fit fine.\nDo you have the other armors we commissioned?
\rOrion? \pn?\nWhat on earth are you two doing here?
\bI just walked through the door. It wasn't guarded or anything.
\rOh... right. I should probably get on that.
\rWhy are you here, though?\nShouldn't you be managing your Gym?
\bI came because my friend told me to. There was s-
\bYou, again! Stay away from me and my pal!\nI don't know what you want, but you'll never put your hands on them!
\bIt really is adorable, how brave kids are.
\bI appreciate you coming though. This saves me the trouble of finding Reshiram myself.
\bBehold, child, the titan of the Unova region.\nZekrom, the Dragon of Ideals!
\bNow bound in protective armor, it is stronger and tougher than ever before!
\bIt's the perfect fusion of both Pokemon and machine.
\bWhy would it choose to join forces with something like you?
\bIt didn't. I caught it.\nIt's very easy to get a Pokemon to obey you once you've tamed it.
\bThen why don't you try and stop me?
\bHow about it? A double or nothing battle between the two of us.
\bA duel between dragons... winner takes all.
\bUnless, of course, you don't care about what happens to Zekrom.
\bI do care... but you have a suit of armor!\nThat isn't fair at all!
\bI guess not, then. What a disappointment.\nI'll be on my way.
\bI don't know what on earth your problem is, but I'll be gosh-darned if you're going to walk all over me, too!
\bWe... we're not doing any damage at all!
\bZekrom, this is getting boring. Finish it.
\bIt looks like an armored legendary Pokemon is able to take out an armor-less one.
\bThat's pretty indicative of the power of these armors, if you ask me.
\bDo you think that you can beat the perfect combination of science and myth?
\bBring it on. I want payback for what happened in Helios City!
\bThe armor seems to still have a few glitches left to fix.
\bIt shows potential, but it's definitely not complete yet.
\bOrion, is it? You want Reshiram back?\nVisit the Dragon Ruins near Selene City, that's where I'll be.
\bHumanity and Pokemon are two sides of the same coin.\nEach can do unique things the other couldn't hope to try.
\bIf we could combine the talents of both people and Pokemon...
\rWhat a nutcase. That's the craziest thing I've heard in my life.
\bAnastasia, aren't the ruins near Selene City the ones that are totally off-limits?
\bI have to, Anastasia.\nI need to do it for Reshiram.
\bIt was my friend before I even knew it was a Pokemon.
\bIt's supported me even when the entire city was against me.
\bYou're dead wrong if you think I'll abandon it now.
\rListen, \pn. Don't judge me about the armor thing.
\rI didn't know he was a cultist until today. I'd never even seen him before.
\rAnd hey- if it helps any, I have a few prototype armor suits.
\rThey're not perfect, but they'll get the job done. Let me know if you're interested.
\rAll right, Taen, your commission is done.

\rWell, it does what you'd expect armor to do.
\rIt increases your defense a tiny bit and makes you more resilient to attacks.

\bI've been working for Anastasia for two to three years.
\bI don't do so well with other people, so it's nice to just bury my head in work sometimes.
\bLet me teach you a few of the things I've learned.
\bWhat can I teach you?\ch[2,8,Iron Head,Magnet Rise,Iron Defense,Meteor Mash,Zap Cannon,Electro Ball,Shift Gear,(Cancel)]
\bOh, a shame. Maybe another time, then.
